---
name: {{ name | tojson }}
description: {{ description | tojson }}
kind: meta
meta_priority: {{ meta_priority | default(50) }}
always: false
triggers:
{%- for t in triggers %}
  - {{ t | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
provenance:
  origin: opensquilla-user
  license: Apache-2.0
metadata:
  opensquilla:
    risk: "low"
    read_only: true
    no_write: true
    write_access: false
    network_access: false
    creator_gates:
      - "G1 structural lint"
      - "G2 scheduler dry-run"
      - "G3 positive trigger smoke"
      - "G4 unrelated negative smoke"
      - "acceptance_compare versus highest-tier no-meta baseline"
      - "runtime_e2e versus highest-tier no-meta baseline"
composition:
  steps:
{%- for step in steps %}
    - id: {{ step.id }}
{%- if creator_step_kind is defined %}
{%- set step_kind = creator_step_kind(step.skill) %}
{%- else %}
{%- set step_kind = "agent" %}
{%- endif %}
{%- if step_kind in ["skill_exec", "llm_chat"] %}
      kind: {{ step_kind }}
{%- endif %}
      skill: {{ step.skill | tojson }}
      read_only: true
      write_access: false
      network_access: false
{%- if not loop.first %}
      depends_on: [{{ steps[loop.index0 - 1].id }}]
{%- endif %}
      with:
{%- if step.with_keys %}
{%- for k, v in step.with_keys.items() %}
        {{ k }}: {{ v | tojson }}
{%- endfor %}
{%- elif step_kind == "skill_exec" and step.skill == "history-explorer" %}
        query: "{{ step.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
        window_days: "30"
        include: "co_occurrences,meta_usage,router_fixtures"
{%- elif step_kind == "skill_exec" and step.skill == "git-diff" %}
        mode: cached_fallback_worktree
        cwd: "{{ '{{' }} inputs.workspace_dir | default('.') {{ '}}' }}"
{%- else %}
{%- if loop.first %}
        task: "{{ step.task }}: {{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(512) {{ '}}' }}"
{%- else %}
        task: {{ step.task | tojson }}
        user_request: "{{ '{{' }} inputs.user_message | xml_escape | truncate(1200) {{ '}}' }}"
        prior_outputs:
{%- for prev in steps[:loop.index0] %}
          {{ prev.id }}: "{{ '{{' }} outputs.{{ prev.id }} | truncate(2000) {{ '}}' }}"
{%- endfor %}
{%- endif %}
{%- endif %}
{%- endfor %}
---

# {{ name }} (Meta-Skill, P3 condition_gated)

{{ description }}

## Execution Flow
{%- for step in steps %}

{{ loop.index }}. `{{ step.id }}` runs `{{ step.skill }}`.
   Purpose: {{ step.task }}
{%- endfor %}

## Expected Output

Return a decision-ready final artifact with explicit assumptions, missing-data
limits, and next actions. Keep claims grounded in the step outputs.

## Safety

This proposal is read-only and keeps all generated step inputs escaped or
bounded for gate review.

## Creator Gates

Generated proposals must pass structural lint, scheduler dry-run, trigger
smoke tests, collision/risk checks, acceptance comparison, and runtime E2E
comparison before auto-enable eligibility.
